## Anti-example (❌ do NOT capture this kind of entry here)

```
### AD-XXX — Never use jQuery
- Tried: never.
- Abandoned because: it's old.
```

**Why this is wrong:** This is not an anti-decision, this is a prejudice.
There was no attempt, no measurement, no learning. If there's a real reason
the project avoids jQuery (e.g., bundle size budget, security audit of
versions, team skill on modern alternatives), then either (a) it's a business
rule about bundle policy (`business-rules.md`), or (b) it's a vendor decision
(`vendor-relationships.md` explaining why React/Vue/Svelte was chosen).

Empty grievances dilute this file's signal. Each entry must carry a story
that took real engineering time.

